ce University majoring in computer science but with deep interests in physics. I am currently working at Rice University to recover data from partially damaged telescope data using machine learning and developing my ability to solve interdisciplinary problems in both physics and computer science. </p>\n<p>Here's a few technologies I've been working with recently:</p>"}}]},"jobs":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Undergraduate Researcher","company":"Solar Physics Research Group","location":"Houston, TX","range":"August 2019 - Present","url":"http://solar.rice.edu/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Develop machine learning algorithm (Random Forest) to recover damaged data from a telescope</li>\n<li>Verify data recovered using previous data under a similar physical condition</li>\n<li>Ensure the entirety of the data before a new telescope is deployed and make the algorithm applicable to other data recovery job</li>\n</ul>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Management Intern","company":"Polaris & Dawn Consulting","location":"Beijing, CN","range":"June - August 2019","url":"http://www.polarisanddawn.com/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Developed a course scheduling system using Python (pandas) to accelerate the workflow</li>\n<li>Used Google Map API to develop configured maps to help customers understand different school</li>\n<li>Proposed and implemented the automated scheduling and feedback system between consultants, teachers and clients and saved 10 hours/week of manual work</li>\n</ul>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Undergraduate Research Assistant","company":"T.W.Bonner Nuclear Laboratory","location":"Houston, TX","range":"May - July 2017","url":"http://bonnerlab.rice.edu/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Analyzed the data of tens of millions of collisions of J/psi mesons and strange charm mesons collected from LHC</li>\n<li>Used boost decision tree, rectangular cut and MLP to train the data to get a better selection of the signal through TMVA</li>\n<li>Manipulated data stored in trees and visualized them via ROOT</li>\n<li>Optimized the C++ software in the Linux environment and increased the signal significance by 200%</li>\n</ul>"}}]},"featured":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"OctoProfile","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='400'%20height='250'%3e%3cpath%20d='M0%2081v80h50v-10l1-10h94v20h8v-10l1-10h93v10l1%2010h7v-10l1-10h94v10l1%2010h50V0H0v81m192-65c-8%204-11%2014-7%2022%202%204%201%204%207%200%205-4%205-4%205%203-1%207%200%208%205%206%203%200%203%200%202-7l1-7%201%202%203%204c5%201%205%201%206-2%207-14-10-29-23-21m95%20171c0%206%200%206%203%206%206%202%2010%209%208%2015l-1%203%205%203%205%203%201-2%202-9c1-11-6-20-17-24-6-2-6-2-6%205m-222%202c-3%203-6%208-6%2010s21%207%2022%206l-13-18c0-1-2%200-3%202m13%2019c-12%2014-13%2016-4%2018%207%203%2015%202%2020-2l2-2-7-8-7-9-4%203'%20fill='%2364ffda'%20fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":1.6008004002001,"src":"/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/e8606/octoprofile.png","srcSet":"/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/53aff/octoprofile.png 175w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/1844f/octoprofile.png 350w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/e8606/octoprofile.png 700w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/c9f12/octoprofile.png 1050w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/ea5f8/octoprofile.png 1400w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/a7eed/octoprofile.png 3200w","srcWebp":"/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/93ec8/octoprofile.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/61503/octoprofile.webp 175w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/850cb/octoprofile.webp 350w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/93ec8/octoprofile.webp 700w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/fbd0c/octoprofile.webp 1050w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/f0780/octoprofile.webp 1400w,\n/static/193dbee3a936d593a166559259d32c67/4b3a0/octoprofile.w